The Nigerian Airforce has directed all applicants who have applied for the NAF Basic Training Course to check their names in the NAF portal. Edward Gabkwet Air Commodore, Director of Public Relations and Information Nigerian Air Force, in a statement on Wednesday, said the recruitment selection is scheduled to hold from 27 June to 28 August 2022 at NAF Base, Kaduna. “This is to inform the general public and all applicants that applied for the Nigerian Air Force (NAF) Basic Military Training Course (BMTC) 43/2022 to visit the NAF recruitment portal at www.nafrecruitment.airforce.mil.ng to check the list of shortlisted candidates. “The Recruitment Selection Board Interviews, divided in 8 batches, are scheduled to hold from 27 June to 28 August 2022 at NAF Base, Kaduna,” the statement said. It informed all candidates attending the Selection Board to be of high disciplinary standard during the screening exercises, adding that anything short of this, will not be tolerated.